OL,6,FITV News' Business and Economics
OL,7,FEditor Joel Hills said it "leaves the
OL,8,Fdoor open" to an interest rate cut in
OL,9,FJune.
OL,11,FBoE Governor Andrew Bailey signalled
OL,12,Fas much optimism, saying: "We've had
OL,13,Fencouraging news on inflation and we
OL,14,Fthink it will fall close to our 2%
OL,15,Ftarget in the next couple of months.
OL,17,F"We need to see more evidence that
OL,18,Finflation will stay low before we can
OL,19,Fcut interest rates. I'm optimistic
OL,20,Fthat things are moving in the right
OL,21,Fdirection."
