OL,3,CBank of England keeps interest rates
OL,4,Cunchanged at 5.25%
OL,6,FBetween March 2009 and May 2022 the
OL,7,FBoE held interest rates at below 1%.
OL,9,FBut ever since, rates have been
OL,10,Fsharply rising - peaking at 5.25% in
OL,11,FAugust 2023.
OL,13,FIn three months (September - December
OL,14,F2022) rates jumped from 2.25% to 3.5%,
OL,15,Ffollowing the announcement of former
OL,16,Fprime minister Liz Truss' mini-budget.
OL,18,FThe last time rates reached 5.25% was
OL,19,Fduring the 2008 financial crisis.
OL,21,FWhat are interest rates?
