OL,6,FIf you borrow from lenders (e.g.
OL,7,Fbanks), the interest rate is the
OL,8,Famount you are charged for borrowing
OL,9,Fmoney. It is shown as a percentage of
OL,10,Fthe total amount of the loan.
OL,12,FIn contrast, if you are a saver, the
OL,13,Fsavings rate tells you how much money
OL,14,Fwill be paid into your account, as a
OL,15,Fpercentage of your savings.
